28/10/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Around 84 per cent of the public believes Greece will organise a successful summer Olympiad next year, according to a poll published Monday (27 October) in <I>Kathimerini</I>. 
Only 3.5 per cent said the Games would fail, while another 9.6 per cent believe they will probably not be a success. 
The public was less optimistic about the situation after the Games: nearly 38 per cent fear increased unemployment and 25 per cent expect economic recession. 
(Kathimerini - 27/10/03)
